<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,624,865]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,624,649]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Collar of pronotum with lateral corners distinctly prominent, obtuse-angular (
<figureCitation box="[1159,1232,624,649]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1955,1977]" captionTargetBox="[169,1405,193,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[169,1405,193,1928]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 6. Pediobius crassicornis (Thomson, 1878). a: female, body in dorsal view; b: female, body in lateral view; c: male, body in dorsal view; d: female, body in lateral view; e: female, fore wing. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/375765/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Figs 6</figureCitation>
a, 6c, 7a, 7c). The posterior margin of MLM strongly emarginate and slightly raised, separated from the base of scutellum with a distinct, narrow semicircular hole (
<figureCitation box="[541,612,696,721]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1955,1977]" captionTargetBox="[169,1405,193,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[169,1405,193,1928]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 6. Pediobius crassicornis (Thomson, 1878). a: female, body in dorsal view; b: female, body in lateral view; c: male, body in dorsal view; d: female, body in lateral view; e: female, fore wing. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/375765/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Figs 6</figureCitation>
a, 6c, 7a, 7c). Notaular depressions deep. Inner corner of axilla depressed. Scutellum smooth at least in anterior median third. Metatibial spur curved and at least reaching the apex of basal tarsomere (
<figureCitation box="[277,344,768,793]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1911,1933]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,371,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,369,1890]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 7. Pediobius elasmi (Ashmead, 1904). a: female, body in dorsal view; b: female, mesosoma + metasoma in lateral view; c: male, body in dorsal view; d: male, body in lateral view; e: female, fore wing; f: female, hind leg; g: female, antenna; h: male, antenna. Scale bar: a – d, 0.5 mm; e, 0.4 mm; f – h, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/375766/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
f).
</paragraph>
